### [Haggai Chapter 1](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#001.md)

[Haggai 1:1](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">hag 1:1</span></span>

Son - Adoptive son to Shealtiel, being of the royal line, but by nature,
son of Pedaiah. Governor - Appointed to this by the Persian king, over
the remnant returned out of Babylon. Joshua - A type of the great
deliverer; one Joshua leads them into Canaan, another restores the
temple.

[Haggai 1:4](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">hag 1:4</span></span>

Ceiled - Arched and richly adorned.

[Haggai 1:6](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">hag 1:6</span></span>

Have not enough - But what you eat doth not nourish or satisfy you. Are
not filled - Your water quenches not your thirst, your wine does not
revive your spirit. None warm - You have no comfort therein. With holes
- Loses all his labour.

[Haggai 1:8](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">hag 1:8</span></span>

Take pleasure - I will accept your offerings, and hear your prayers.
Glorified - Shew my majesty and account myself glorified by you also.

[Haggai 1:9](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">hag 1:9</span></span>

Came to little - But it answered not the expectation. I did blow - I
blasted it. Ye run - You with eagerness carry on your own particular
buildings.

[Haggai 1:10](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">hag 1:10</span></span>

Is stayed - God hath forbidden them, to drop down dew.

[Haggai 1:11](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">hag 1:11</span></span>

Upon men - The very blood, and constitutions of men were changed, and
many diseases afflicted them.

[Haggai 1:13](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">hag 1:13</span></span>

In the Lord's message - ln the words of his master. The people - The
whole assembly.

[Haggai 1:14](../../../bib/kjv/hag001.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">hag 1:14</span></span>

The Lord of hosts - By which name he delights to be known among the
returned captives; and it was a name best suited to their present state,
compassed on all hands with enemies.

